The People ex rel. Albert Kocourek v. The City of Chicago and Mandel Bros.Opinion filed December 18, 1901.This case is controlled by the decision in People ex rel. v. City of , Chicago and Sehlesinger & Mayer, {ante, p. 507.)

Mageudee, J., dissenting.

Original petition for mandamus.L. P. Wilcox, for relator.Charles H. Walker, Corporation Counsel, for respondent the city of Chicago.Dupee, Judah, Willard & Wolf, for respondents Handel Bros. Per Curiam

This case being in all respects like that of People ex rel. v. City of Chicago and Schlesinger & Mayer, (ante, p. 507,) the writ will be denied for the reasons stated in the opinion filed in that case.

Writ denied.

Mr. Justice Magruder

I do not think the writ ought to be denied for reasons stated in Marshall Field and Sehlesinger & Mayer cases, (ante, pp. 525 and 543.)
